.TH lgamma 3
.SH NAME
.PP
\*Llgamma\*O \- Computes the logarithm of the gamma function
.SH LIBRARY
.PP
\*OMath Library (\*Llibm.a\*O)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.sS
\*L#include <math.h>
.PP
\*Ldouble lgamma  (double \*Vx\*L);
.nL
\*Lfloat  lgammaf (float  \*Vx\*L);\*O
.sE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.iX "lgamma function"
.iX "lgamma_max_float"
\*Llgamma(\|)\*O and \*Llgammaf(\|)\*O
return the logarithm of the absolute
value of \*Vx\*O, or ln(|G(\*Vx\*O)|). The sign of the lgamma of x is
returned in  the external integer variable signgam.
The \*Vx\*O parameter cannot be a nonpositive integer.
.\".iS
